<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-01-15T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-01-15T20:00:00-05:00" n="3" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d3">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A4 General Committee (Arms)/81:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the American Adviser</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Mayer</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-01-15T20:00:00-05:00">January 15, 1935—8 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>466. Your 962, January 15, 1 p.m. We approve, in general, the views
                                and the procedure outlined in the penultimate paragraph, but do not
                                want to assume the position of forcing the hands of Great Britain
                                and France. Your best approach would seem to be to state that while
                                we wish in no manner to interfere with or hamper any major political
                                negotiations, we do not quite understand why simultaneous work of a
                                purely technical nature at Geneva should have this effect, and that
                                we would view with great regret any undue delay in the resumption of
                                the technical work of the Committees.</p>
                            <p>Your 963, January 15, 4 p.m.<note n="12" xml:id="d3fn12">Not
                                    printed.</note> Approved.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>